<p>Rachel Andrew is a web developer with skills both in server-side languages and front-end development. She has written numerous acclaimed books, including <i>The CSS Anthology: 101 Essential Tips, Tricks & Hacks</i>, <i>HTML Utopia: Designing Without Tables Using CSS</i>, and <i>Everything You Know About CSS is Wrong</i>. Rachel is the director of <a href="http://www.edgeofmyseat.com/" title="Edge Of My Seat">edgeofmyseat.com</a>, and she co-created <a href="http://grabaperch.com/" title="Perch">Perch</a>, the really little, super-efficient content management system.</p>
<p>Rachel has <a href="http://www.rachelandrew.co.uk/" title="Rachel's Journal">a personal website</a>, and tweets <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/rachelandrew" title="Rachel's Twitter Account">@rachelandrew</a>.</p>